  {panel}

Using an image tag such as \!blah.jpg|thumnail! and performing an export to HTML results in a link back to the server the image was exported from rather than the local exported directory. 

Here is an example exported image with a thumbnail: 

{noformat}
<p><span class="image-wrap" style=""><a class="confluence-thumbnail-link 500x466" href='http://localhost:8080/confluence/download/attachments/2457648/river.jpg'><img src="attachments/thumbnails/2457648/2785284" width="100" style="border: 0px solid black"/></a></span></p>
{noformat}

Assume that I have a page in 'space1' with the following page content:

{code}
[Go to anchor|#anch1]

some text

h2. my title {anchor:anch1}

more text
{code}

You know, clicking "Go to anchor" will make the browser jump to "h2. mytitle".

Then, after I move this page to 'space2',  the first line of that page becomes:

{code}
[Go to anchor|space2:#anch1]
{code}

thus the local-page link is broken!

