We are currently building a space which serves to display industry news (clipped from newsletters) filtered by various criteria. For this purpose we use {blog-posts} with associated labels and match-labels=all to allow for detailed filtering of the displayed news.
In parallel we also intended to offer the news-content of each page as RSS-feed; this is however not possible in the more advanced filter cases, since the feed-builder only supports disjunction of labels.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-8307].
  {panel}

Currently, LDAP users must be authenticated in OSUser by doing a bind (i.e. by logging in) then performing a search.

Some LDAP servers are configured to deny users access to search, and we could support those servers by allowing users to customise whether the search is performed as part of the authentication or not.

